  "text": "Spleens were mechanically minced, and mononuclear cells were isolated by use of a Ficoll (Biochrom) gradient. Cells (4ϫ10 [CITATION_1] ) were seeded into fibronectin (Sigma)-coated 24-well plates in 0.5 mL endothelial basal medium (CellSystems). After 7 days in culture, cells were stained for 1,1Ј-dioctadecyl-3,3,3Ј,3Ј-tetramethylindocarbocyanine perchlorate (DiI-Ac-LDL, CellSystems) and FITClabeled lectin (UEA-1, Sigma). At least 3 high-power fields of each well were analyzed. Cells positive for DiI-Ac-LDL and lectin staining were judged to be EPCs and were counted.",
